pip3 install ansible


create directory
go inside
"touch inventory"
install sublime text
"subl ."


inventory group of servers -> list the servers, can be ip or name



ansible -i inventory --private-key ansibletest.pem example -m ping -u ec2-user


after configuring user and ec2 pem file in ansible.cfg
ansible example -m ping(ping module)
ansible example -a "free -h" -> running commands against server


-m -> module -> by default ansible uses command module
-a -> arguments, 

arguments used till now -> free -h, date

modules: command, script, yum, service


